			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	VoucherCodes.co.uk is one of the UK&rsquo;s largest money saving web sites with almost 4.6 million members. We are looking for an enthusiastic graduate with excellent communication skills and a passion for the web to join our Partnerships team at our Central London offices.</p>
<p>
	Your role will involve managing and building up relationships with the retailers we feature. As part of this you&rsquo;ll be securing the very best online discounts for our users from the likes of Marks and Spencer, Boden, Expedia, Debenhams, Amazon as well as many of the smaller retailers on our site who are equally vital to our business. We love getting our users the best deal on everything from a new party dress to a holiday in Rome so we&rsquo;re looking for someone who&rsquo;s just as passionate about online shopping as we are.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Forge strong relations with retailers featured on VoucherCodes.co.uk</li>
	<li>
		Acting as the first point of contact for advertisers and retailers, networks and agencies, and responding to their requests and concerns as necessary.</li>
	<li>
		Negotiation of exclusive deals and partnerships and better rates for VoucherCodes.co.uk with retailers and affiliate networks.</li>
	<li>
		Analysing the performance of retailers discounts and feeding back results</li>
	<li>
		Actively pitching VoucherCodes.co.uk to new retailers, advertisers and media partners.</li>
	<li>
		Identifying new opportunities within your assigned retailers and networks, and then proactively targeting these opportunities</li>
	<li>
		Liaise with the Publishing Editor to coordinate seasonal promotions with retailers.</li>
	<li>
		Liaise with our PR team to coordinate discounts for newspapers and other media partners</li>
	<li>
		Administrative duties, such as competitor monitoring, adding content to our site and responding to user queries.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>About you</strong></p>
<p>
	All training will be provided, but essentially, we are looking for someone who is:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Graduate with a 2:1 Degree from a Red Brick University</li>
	<li>
		Confident, articulate &lsquo;people person&rsquo; with excellent communication skills</li>
	<li>
		Self-motivated and pragmatic - Works well to targets and happy to take on responsibility for multiple deliverables and projects working independently and as part of a team</li>
	<li>
		Persuasive &ndash; able to convince retailers and networks to provide VoucherCodes.co.uk with the very best deals</li>
	<li>
		Tenacious and resilient &ndash; overcomes setbacks quickly and identifies new approaches when required.</li>
	<li>
		Comfortable presenting / speaking on phone etc..</li>
	<li>
		Good numeracy skills - Competent working with numbers and basic statistical data.</li>
	<li>
		Super organised &ndash; able to multitask and thrives working towards targets and deadlines.</li>
	<li>
		Commercially savvy</li>
	<li>
		Loves the web and comfortable learning new interfaces and programmes.</li>
</ul>
